parameters.description: The encounter that this diagnostic order is associated with (Encounter).

parameters.name: event-date
parameters.description: The date at which the event happened. The date parameter format is yyyy-mm-ddThh:nn:ss(TZ). The prefixes >, >=, <= and < may be used on the parameter value.

parameters.name: event-date
parameters.description: The date parameter format is yyyy-mm-ddThh:nn:ss(TZ). Two dates can be used to specify an interval. The prefixes >, >=, <= and < may be used on the parameter value.

parameters.name: event-status
parameters.description: proposed | draft | planned | requested | received | accepted | in-progress | review | completed | cancelled | suspended | rejected | failed. Value can have following formats: [code] or [system]|[code] or |[code].

parameters.name: event-status-date
parameters.description: A combination of past-status and date. Value should be in the form: [status]$[date]

parameters.name: identifier
parameters.description: Identifiers assigned to this order. Value can have following formats: [code] or [system]|[code] or |[code].

parameters.name: item-date
parameters.description: The date at which the event happened. The date parameter format is yyyy-mm-ddThh:nn:ss(TZ). The prefixes >, >=, <= and < may be used on the parameter value.

parameters.name: item-date
parameters.description: The date at which the event happened. The date parameter format is yyyy-mm-ddThh:nn:ss(TZ). Two dates can be used to specify an interval. The prefixes >, >=, <= and < may be used on the parameter value.

parameters.name: item-past-status
parameters.description: proposed | draft | planned | requested | received | accepted | in-progress | review | completed | cancelled | suspended | rejected | failed. Value can have following formats: [code] or [system]|[code] or |[code].

parameters.name: item-status
parameters.description: proposed | draft | planned | requested | received | accepted | in-progress | review | completed | cancelled | suspended | rejected | failed. Value can have following formats: [code] or [system]|[code] or |[code].

parameters.name: item-status-date
parameters.description: A combination of item-past-status and item-date. Value should be in the form: [status]$[date]

parameters.name: orderer
parameters.description: Who ordered the test (Practitioner).

parameters.name: patient
parameters.description: Who and/or what test is about (Patient).

parameters.name: specimen
parameters.description: If the whole order relates to specific specimens (Specimen).

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: proposed | draft | planned | requested | received | accepted | in-progress | review | completed | cancelled | suspended | rejected | failed. Value can have following formats: [code] or [system]|[code] or |[code].

parameters.name: subject
parameters.description: Who and/or what test is about (Device, Location, Patient, Group).
